PhD Graduate - Digital IC Design, Singapore
This is a superb opportunity for a highly qualified (PhD) candidate with experience in digital SoC design to join a world leading Singapore based R&D; organisation.
In this role you will be responsible for digital integrated circuit activities for applications in Biomedical, MEMS and other digital design areas.
The successful applicant will be PhD qualified (or equivalent) in a relevant Science/Engineering field with strong emphasis on digital IC design and have established experience in low power digital integrated circuit design. There is great scope to progress to a leadership/technical management position.
Remuneration will include a high basic salary and excellent benefits, including relocation and allowances.
If you would like to be part of a world renowned R&D; company in an exciting location please send your CV to IC Resources today.
Key words: World-leading biomedical research organisation seeks a PhD qualified digital IC design engineer. Skills required: digital, IC, ASIC, design, RTL, VHDL, Verilog, low power, nano electronics, SoC, integrated circuit design, semiconductor, job
